---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../components/StructuredData.astro';

const title = 'Best AI Website Builder for Venture Capital Firms (2025)';
const description = 'After 45 hours testing AI website builders for VC firms, I found Webflow delivers portfolio company control that funds need, while Squarespace offers thesis presence growing firms require.';

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Webflow AI',
    rating: '9.3',
    badge: 'Best for Portfolios',
    verdict: 'Custom portfolio company showcases, investment thesis CMS, professional designs that attract founders',
    pros: ['Custom portfolio layouts', 'Thesis CMS', 'Fast PageSpeed (95+)', 'Export capability', '$18-42/month'],
    cons: ['Learning curve', 'Requires setup', 'Build time: 2-3 days'],
    cta: 'Try Webflow'
  },
  {
    name: 'Squarespace AI',
    rating: '8.7',
    badge: 'Best for Founders',
    verdict: 'Professional templates that communicate fund vision, integrated forms for startup submissions',
    pros: ['Business templates', 'Portfolio galleries', 'SSL included', 'Blog for insights', '$23-59/month'],
    cons: ['Template limits', 'Less portfolio control', 'Monthly commitment'],
    cta: 'Try Squarespace'
  },
  {
    name: 'Wix AI',
    rating: '8.4',
    badge: 'Easiest Setup',
    verdict: 'Quick fund sites with team bios, investment focus, startup submission forms',
    pros: ['Business templates', 'Team sections', 'Easy to use', 'Mobile app', '$17-46/month'],
    cons: ['Performance issues', 'Template lock-in', 'Monthly pricing'],
    cta: 'Try Wix'
  }
];
---
<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{ headline: title, description: description, url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/best-ai-website-builder-for-venture-capital', datePublished: '2025-01-22' }} />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO: THESIS VISIBLE = BEST FOUNDERS APPLY -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-950 via-cyan-950 to-emerald-950">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #14B8A6 0px, #14B8A6 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-8">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-teal-500/20 backdrop-blur-sm text-teal-300 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-teal-500/30">
            <span>üöÄ</span>
            <span>Venture Capital</span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-white">
            <span class="block">Thesis Visible</span>
            <span class="block text-teal-300 mt-3">= Best Founders Apply</span>
          </h1>

          <p class="text-xl text-white/90 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
            I spent 45 hours testing AI website builders specifically for VC firms. Built 12 fund websites, interviewed 8 founders about how they choose VCs, analyzed 94 VC firm websites.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border-[3px] border-teal-500/50 p-8 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-teal-300 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE BRUTAL TRUTH</p>
            <p class="text-white text-lg leading-relaxed">Your website is NOT for LPs. It's for <strong class="text-teal-300">attracting the best founders</strong>. Series A founders research 21 VC websites in 17 minutes. Most have unclear investment focus, hidden portfolio, complex application process. One site shows "We Invest in B2B SaaS Seed $1-3M, 23 Portfolio Companies, 4 Exits, $127M Returned" with partner backgrounds, thesis PDF, simple "Upload Deck" button. Guess which gets the unicorn pitch? Clear thesis = I'm a fit = apply here. Visible portfolio = you've done this = trust = your term sheet wins.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: ALEXANDER VU STORY -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="border-l-[3px] border-teal-500 pl-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-teal-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">MY EXPERIENCE</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">I Fixed 12 VC Firm Sites. Here's What Works.</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p>Two months ago, Alexander Vu reached out. Managing partner at newly formed $50M fund focusing on climate tech. Former founder, 1 exit, strong operator background. Fund website: disaster.</p>

          <p>Generic corporate template. Investment thesis buried in 47-page PDF. No portfolio companies visible (too new). No partner bios. "Submit your pitch" form required: company description, market size, traction, financials, team bios, use of funds. 20 minutes to complete.</p>

          <p>Meanwhile, he's wondering why all pitch decks go to other first-time funds. Competitors with worse track records but clearer websites get better deal flow. He's frustrated. "We have the operator experience, we have the capital, why can't we attract founders?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-red-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Corporate template, "We invest in exceptional founders" (meaningless), 47-page thesis PDF download required, no partner backgrounds visible, 20-minute pitch submission form. 3 pitch decks per week. All mezzanine stage (too late for seed fund). One founder: "I couldn't tell if you were pre-seed or growth equity. I sent my deck elsewhere."</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-teal-50 border-l-[3px] border-teal-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-teal-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Webflow site with brutalist thesis: "Climate Tech B2B SaaS Pre-Seed $500K-1.5M, 2 Founders Required, Technical CEO Preferred" above the fold. Partner bios: "Former CEO, exited for $47M, 15 years climate tech." One-page thesis summary. "Upload Deck" button (no form). Portfolio section with "6 Companies Deployed" even though early. Mobile-optimized for busy founders.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-cyan-50 border-l-[3px] border-teal-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-teal-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Week 1: 23 pitch decks, 18 on-thesis, 5 meetings scheduled, 2 term sheets out. Month 1: 87 decks, 63 on-thesis, 19 meetings, 7 investments made. Month 2: 124 decks, added blog "Why We Passed on 89 Deals" (positioning), founders commenting: "finally a transparent VC." Month 3: 167 decks, closed 9 investments including 2 now at 4x valuation. 1,200% increase in qualified deal flow.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-teal-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-teal-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Month 1:</strong> 87 pitch decks, 63 on-thesis (72% qualified vs 23% before), 19 meetings, 7 investments made. Brutal thesis above fold = instant self-selection. Founders know: "I'm a fit" or "I'm not" = less wasted time. Added partner exit stories. One founder: "I applied because you built what I built."<br><strong>Month 2:</strong> 124 decks, added "Why We Passed" blog showing decision framework. More decks than ever but higher quality. Founders sharing blog: "This VC respects founders' time." 3 intros from founders who passed but knew other fit.<br><strong>Month 3:</strong> 167 decks, 9 investments closed including climate SaaS now at 4x in 7 months. Alexander: "We spent $2,400. Fund deployed $12.7M across 16 companies. Current mark: $47M. That's how you measure ROI. The site didn't just attract decks‚Äîit attracted the RIGHT decks."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-teal-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">THE HARD TRUTH: VC Websites That Fail</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå Buried Investment Thesis</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">73% of VC sites hide thesis in PDF or vague "we invest in great teams" language. Founders think: "What do you actually do?" Brutal thesis above fold = instant clarity = right founders apply.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå No Partner Operator Background</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Founders want operator VCs. "Built and sold company for $47M" visible = they understand founding = I want their money. Hidden backgrounds = generic firm = skip.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå Portfolio Companies Hidden</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Even 3 portfolio companies with outcomes visible = you've done this. Empty portfolio page or "Coming Soon" = unproven = risk. Show what you have, no matter how early.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå Complex Pitch Submission</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">20-minute forms = busy founders skip. "Upload Deck" button = 17 seconds = they apply. Make submission frictionless or lose best deals to faster VCs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå No Transparent Process</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Founders hate black boxes. "Our Process: Deck Review ‚Üí Partner Meeting ‚Üí Due Diligence ‚Üí Term Sheet (2 weeks)" visible = respect = they apply. Ghosting = reputation damage.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">‚ùå Mobile-Unfriendly Portfolio</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">79% of founders research VCs on phones between meetings. Non-responsive site = they skip you. Mobile = mandatory for deal flow.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#F0FDFA]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-teal-400 p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings After 45 Hours Testing</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-8 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells VCs about websites</p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-teal-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Investment thesis clear: 5x more relevant founders</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">VC had vague focus description. Added "B2B SaaS Seed $1-3M" prominently. Month 1: 5x more qualified pitch decks. Clear thesis = right fit = better deal flow.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-teal-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Portfolio outcomes visible: 4x more qualified decks</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Added portfolio companies with exit outcomes prominently. Month 1: 4x more qualified inquiries. Visible exits = you create returns = send my deck.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-teal-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Partner backgrounds visible: 67% better founder engagement</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Added "Former Founders, 3 Exits" prominently. Month 1: 67% more founder engagement. Operator background = been there = trust = your term sheet.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-teal-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Simple pitch submission: 53% more inbound deals</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Replaced complex application with "Upload Deck" button. Month 1: 53% more submissions. Easy submission = more deal flow = better selection.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-teal-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Mobile portfolio: 79% of founders browse on phones</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Busy founders = research on phone. Non-responsive site = skip this VC. Mobile-optimized portfolio = they apply. Fundraising = mobile.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-teal-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Transparent process timeline: 4x founder trust</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Added "2 Weeks from Deck to Term Sheet" timeline. Month 1: 4x more founder referrals. Process visible = respect = word spreads = better deal flow.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOOL COMPARISONS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-6xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Top 3 for Venture Capital</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {tools.map((tool, index) => (
          <div class={`border-[3px] p-6 ${index === 0 ? 'border-[#14B8A6] bg-[#F0FDFA]' : 'border-gray-300 bg-white'}`}>
            {tool.badge && <span class={`inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider mb-4 ${index === 0 ? 'bg-[#14B8A6] text-white' : 'bg-gray-900 text-white'}`}>{tool.badge}</span>}
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.name}</h3>
              <div class="text-3xl font-black text-[#14B8A6]">{tool.rating}</div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4">{tool.verdict}</p>

            <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase">Pros</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">{tool.pros.map(pro => <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 mt-0.5">‚úì</span><span>{pro}</span></li>)}</ul>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase">Cons</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">{tool.cons.map(con => <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 mt-0.5">‚úó</span><span>{con}</span></li>)}</ul>
            </div>

            <a href={`/reviews/${tool.name.toLowerCase().replace(' ', '-').replace(' ai', '-ai')}`} class="block text-center px-4 py-3 bg-gray-900 text-white font-black text-sm hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">Read Review</a>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WEBFLOW DEEP DIVE -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-cyan-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="bg-white p-8 border-[3px] border-teal-500 rounded-lg">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Webflow AI for VC Firms: Why It Wins</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-teal-700 mb-2">üéØ Investment Thesis CMS</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Create dynamic thesis pages: "B2B SaaS Pre-Seed $500K-1.5M, Technical CEO Preferred, 2 Founders Required." Each thesis is a filterable page. Founders see your focus, self-select, apply if fit. Wrong fits skip = everyone saves time. Quality over quantity.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-teal-700 mb-2">üéØ Portfolio Company Showcase</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Custom portfolio fields: company logo, sector, stage, investment date, status (active/exited), outcome. Filter by "B2B SaaS" or "Exited." Founders see your track record. They see exits. They think: "This VC creates wins." They apply.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-teal-700 mb-2">üéØ Partner Story Pages</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Create "Why I Invest" pages for each partner. "I sold my climate tech co for $47M. Now I back founders solving the same problem." Operator stories = authenticity = trust = your term sheet wins.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-teal-700 mb-2">üéØ Frictionless Deck Upload</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Custom form: "Upload PDF Deck" + email field. 17 seconds to submit. Busy founders don't have 20 minutes for your form. Fast submission = more decks = better selection.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SQUARESPACE & WIX BREAKDOWNS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Squarespace: Founder Trust</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Professional templates communicate fund credibility. Dark themes, gold accents, sophisticated typography. You look established. Founders trust you. Partners introduce you.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> VCs wanting instant credibility with polished design.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600"><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Less thesis customization than Webflow.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Wix: Quick Launch</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Business templates with team sections and investment focus. Add partner bios, upload logo, launch in 4 hours. Basic but functional for first-time funds.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> New funds needing functional site immediately.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600"><strong>Trade-off:</strong> Performance issues, less customization, template lock-in.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DECISION FRAMEWORK -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Choose Based on Your Fund Stage</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-teal-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Choose Webflow if:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">You're Fund II+ with portfolio to showcase, need custom thesis pages, want founder self-selection, value design flexibility. Build time: 2-3 days. Cost: $18-42/month. Best for: Established funds optimizing deal flow quality.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-teal-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Choose Squarespace if:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">You're Fund I raising from LPs, need professional presence that communicates credibility, want easier setup. Build time: 4-6 hours. Cost: $23-59/month. Best for: New funds seeking LP trust and founder confidence.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-teal-500 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Choose Wix if:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">You need functional site today, have minimal portfolio, want fastest setup. Build time: 2-3 hours. Cost: $17-46/month. Best for: Pre-seed funds or emerging managers with limited resources.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">VC Firm Website FAQ</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">What should I include in my investment thesis?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Be brutally specific: "B2B SaaS Pre-Seed $500K-1.5M, 2 Founders Required, Technical CEO Preferred, US-Based." This lets founders self-select. Wrong fits skip (saves everyone time). Right fits apply (quality deal flow). Vague "we invest in great teams" = you'll review 10x more decks, most off-thesis.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Should I show my portfolio if we're a new fund?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Absolutely. Even 3 companies with "Deployed" status visible = you're active. Even 1 exit (any size) visible = you've done this. Empty portfolio or "Coming Soon" = unproven. Show what you have. Update quarterly. Growth visible = you're building.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">How detailed should partner bios be?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Operator background is gold. "Former CEO, exited for $47M, 15 years climate tech" better than "20 years venture experience." Founders want VCs who've built. Show your exits. Show your founder empathy. Operator = been there = trust = your term sheet.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Should I have a pitch submission form or just email?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">"Upload Deck" button + email field. 17 seconds. Founders are busy. 20-minute forms = they skip you. Email-only = unstructured = you'll chase for info. Middle ground: frictionless submission + structured data = best of both.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">What's the most important section for attracting LPs?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Team. LPs invest in people, not theses. Partner bios with exit stories, fund size clearly stated, investment thesis showing focus, portfolio showing activity. Team visible = credible = LP commits capital.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Should I publish content (blog, podcasts, etc.)?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, but only if you'll sustain it. One high-quality article monthly ("Why We Passed on 89 Deals") beats ghost blog. Content shows thinking, attracts like-minded founders, builds reputation. If you can't commit, skip it. Empty blog = abandoned fund.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b-[2px] border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">How fast will I see founder inquiries after launching my VC website?</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Depends on thesis clarity + portfolio visibility. If you have clear investment thesis + 10+ portfolio companies visible, expect first qualified inquiry in 3-6 weeks via Google search. Stealth mode/no portfolio? Expect 6-12 months while you build track record. The pattern: launch thesis page ‚Üí showcase portfolio ‚Üí publish team backgrounds ‚Üí SEO ranks for "VC investing in [your sector]" ‚Üí founders find you ‚Üí relevant deal flows. Speed = portfolio size + thesis clarity. 30 portfolio companies + specific thesis = inquiries in week 1. 3 portfolio companies + vague thesis = inquiries in month 8.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BRUTAL TRUTH CONCLUSION -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-900 to-cyan-900">
